OL,6,FInvestigating officer, Detective
OL,7,FInspector Jim Mahon , said: "Our
OL,8,Fthoughts remain with Mrs Mahey's
OL,9,Fchildren and family who continue to
OL,10,Fgrieve for their much loved mother and
OL,11,Floved one.J"This case is a tragic case
OL,12,Fthat has left a family without a
OL,13,Fmother and a father.J""We believe the
OL,14,Fmurder may have been driven by
OL,15,Funsubstantiated jealousy but the true
OL,16,Fmotive may never be known."J"By
OL,17,Fadmitting his guilt he has saved the
OL,18,Ffamily from a lengthy and difficult
OL,19,Ftrial and we hope that this brings a
OL,20,Fsmall comfort to Mrs Mahey's family."
